94// From LROA103.ASM
95//;The format for the serial command is:
96//; S1234<sp>xyWS1234<sp>xyWS1234<sp>xyW<cr><lf>
97//; where 1234 is an ASCII encoded 16 bit command, with the format:
98//; Data Byte for boards: 1 = MSB high nibble, 2 = MSB low nibble
99//; Address Byte for boards: 3 = LSB high nibble, 4 = LSB low nibble
100//; S & W are literal format characters,<sp> = space, xy = CIP address (ignored).
101//; 9 characters are repeated 3 times followed by a carriage return - line feed,
102//; and all alpha characters must be capitalized, baud rate = 1200.
103#define START_COMMAND (uint8*)("S") //Start command string before the 4 command char
104#define START_COMMAND_SIZE 1u //Size of Start command string before the 4 command char
105#define END_COMMAND (uint8*)(" 01W") //End command string after the 4 command char, CIP is 01 which is ignored
106#define END_COMMAND_SIZE 4u //Size of End command string after the 4 command char, CIP is 01 which is ignored
107#define CR (0x0Du) //Carriage return in hex
108#define LF (0x0Au) //Line feed in hex
109#define DLE (0x10u) //Data Link Escape Used as low rate packet header
110#define ETX (0x03u) //Data Link Escape Used as low rate packet trailer
111#define CMD_ID (0x14u) //ID byte for command in low rate packet
112#define REQ_ID (0x13u) //ID byte for request science data in low rate packet
113#define SDATA_ID (0x53u) //ID byte for science data in low rate packet
114#define FILLBYTE (0xA3u) //SPI never transmits so could be anything

743int CmdBytes2String (uint8* in, uint8* out)
744{
745 if ((NULL == in) || (NULL == (in + 1)) || (NULL == out)) //check for null pointers
746 {
747 cntError++;
748 return -EFAULT; //null pointer error, sprint might also do this
749 }
750 return sprintf((char*)out, "%02X%02X", *(in), *(in + 1)); //converts the 2 bytes to hex with leading zerosv
751}
752
753uint8 BCD2Dec( uint8 bcd )
754{
755 return bcd - (6 * (bcd >> 4));
756}
757uint8 Dec2BCD( uint8 dec )
758{
759 uint16 num16 = dec;
760 uint16 num8 = (uint8)((num16 * 103) >> 10);
761 return dec + (6 * num8);
762}

765{

782//
783// }
784 return 0;

787int SendInitCmds()
788{
789 uint16 tempNumCmdLeft = (ACTIVELEN(readBuffCmd[0], writeBuffCmd[0], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE) + NUMBER_INIT_CMDS); //uint16 needed to check if space for commands
790 if (CMD_BUFFER_SIZE <= tempNumCmdLeft) //check if space for commands
791 {
792 cntError++;
793 return -ENOMEM;
794 }
795 tempNumCmdLeft = NUMBER_INIT_CMDS;
796 uint16 tempNumCmdPart = 0;
797 uint8 intState = CyEnterCriticalSection();
798 uint8 tempWrite = writeBuffCmd[0];
799 writeBuffCmd[0] = WRAP(writeBuffCmd[0] + NUMBER_INIT_CMDS, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
800 CyExitCriticalSection(intState);
801 if(CMD_BUFFER_SIZE <= (tempNumCmdLeft + (uint16)tempWrite))
802 {
803 tempNumCmdPart = CMD_BUFFER_SIZE - tempWrite; //commands to end of buffer
804 memcpy(&buffCmd[0][tempWrite][0], initCmd, (tempNumCmdPart * 2));// load all the init commands into 0 buffer
805 tempNumCmdLeft -= tempNumCmdPart;//reduce commands left
806 tempWrite = 0;//start begining of buffer
807 }
808 tempNumCmdPart *= 2;
809 tempNumCmdLeft *= 2;
810// void * debug1 = &(buffCmd[0][tempWrite][0]);//DEBUG
811// void * debug2 = (void *)initCmd + tempNumCmdPart;//DEBUG
812// memcpy(debug1, debug2, tempNumCmdLeft);//DEBUG
813 memcpy(&(buffCmd[0][tempWrite][0]), ((void *)initCmd + tempNumCmdPart), tempNumCmdLeft);// load all the init commands into 0 buffer
814
815 return NUMBER_INIT_CMDS;
816}

855int ParseCmdInputByte(uint8 tempRx, uint8 i)
856{
857 switch(commandStatusC[i])
858 {
859 case WAIT_DLE:
860 if (DLE == tempRx) commandStatusC[i] = CHECK_ID;
861 break;
862 case CHECK_ID:
863 if (CMD_ID == tempRx) commandStatusC[i] = CHECK_LEN;
864 else if (REQ_ID == tempRx) commandStatusC[i] = CHECK_ETX_REQ;
865 else
866 {
867 commandStatusC[i] = WAIT_DLE;
868 cntCmdError++;
869 return -EIDRM;
870 }
871 break;
872 case CHECK_LEN:
873 if(2 == tempRx){
874 commandLenC[i] = tempRx;
875 commandStatusC[i] = READ_CMD;
876 }
877 else
878 {
879 commandStatusC[i] = WAIT_DLE;
880 cntCmdError++;
881 return -E2BIG;
882 }
883 break;
884 case READ_CMD:
885 if(commandLenC[i] > 0)
886 {
887 cmdRxC[i][commandLenC[i] % 2] = tempRx;
888 commandLenC[i]--;
889// buffUsbTxDebug[iBuffUsbTxDebug++] = commandLenC[i]; //debug
890 if(0 == commandLenC[i]) commandStatusC[i]= CHECK_ETX_CMD;
891 }
892
893 break;
894 case CHECK_ETX_CMD:
895 if (ETX == tempRx)
896 {
897
898// int tempRes = CmdBytes2String(cmdRxC[i], curCmd);
899// if(tempRes >= 0)
900// {
901// tempRes = SendCmdString(curCmd); //TODO change this with considerations for commands like RTC set and duplicates
902// if (-EBUSY == tempRes)
903// {
904 if((0x47 == cmdRxC[i][0]) && (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS == cmdRxC[i][1])) // 0x4728 is reset command & needs to be sent in ISR so it can interrrupt hung program
905 {
906 CySoftwareReset(); //software reset
907 }
908 uint8 intState = CyEnterCriticalSection();
909 uint8 tempWrite = writeBuffCmd[i];
910 writeBuffCmd[i] = WRAPINC(writeBuffCmd[i], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
911 CyExitCriticalSection(intState);
912 memcpy(buffCmd[i][tempWrite], cmdRxC[i], 2); //queue for later
913 cntCmd++;
914 lastCmdSource = i; //store last command source
915// }
916// else if (tempRes < 0)
917// {
918// //TODO Error handling
919// }
920// }
921 }
922 else
923 {
924 cntCmdError++;
925 //TODO error
926 return -EILSEQ;
927 }
928 commandStatusC[i] = WAIT_DLE;
929 break;
930 case CHECK_ETX_REQ:
931 if (ETX == tempRx)
932 {
933// SendLRScienceData();
934 lowRateReq = TRUE;
935 }
936 else
937 {
938 cntCmdError++;
939 //TODO error
940 return -EILSEQ;
941 }
942 commandStatusC[i] = WAIT_DLE;
943 break;
944 }
945 return 0;
946}

1031int CheckCmdBuffers()
1032{
1033 if (0 != UART_Cmd_GetTxBufferSize()) return -EBUSY; // Not ready to send
1034 uint8 curChan;
1035 for (uint8 i = 0; i < COMMAND_SOURCES; i++)
1036 {
1037 curChan = orderBuffCmd[i];
1038 if (readBuffCmd[curChan] != writeBuffCmd[curChan]) // check if q has cmd
1039 {
1040 int tempRes = CmdBytes2String(buffCmd[curChan][readBuffCmd[curChan]], curCmd);
1041 tempRes = SendCmdString(curCmd);
1042 readBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(readBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1043 return 1;
1044 }
1045 }
1046 return 0;
1047}
1048
1067int InterpretCmdBuffers()
1068{
1069 uint8 search4Cmd = TRUE, i = 0;
1070 uint8 curChan = orderBuffCmd[i];
1071 uint8 lastAdr;
1072 if (0 == Pin_Reset_Ev_HW_Read())
1073 {
1074 Pin_Reset_Ev_HW_Write(1);
1075 }
1076 if (0 != Pin_Reset_Ev_SW_Read())
1077 {
1078 Pin_Reset_Ev_SW_Write(0);
1079 }
1080 do //search for 1 command for the main PSOC, only interpreting 1 per main program loop
1081 {
1082 if(headerBuffCmd[curChan] == writeBuffCmd[curChan])
1083 {
1084 i++;
1085 if(i < COMMAND_SOURCES)
1086 {
1087 curChan = orderBuffCmd[i];
1088 }
1089 else
1090 {
1091 return 0; //nothing to interpret
1092 }
1093 }
1094 else
1095 {
1096 uint8 headAdr;
1097 if(headerBuffCmd[curChan] == interpretBuffCmd[curChan])
1098 {
1099 headAdr = buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1];
1100 interpretBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1101 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS == (headAdr & CMD_ADDRESS_MASK))
1102 {
1103 if (0 == (headAdr & CMD_NUM_BYTE_MASK))
1104 {
1105 search4Cmd = FALSE;
1106 }
1107 else
1108 {
1109 lastAdr = headAdr;
1110 }
1111 }
1112 else
1113 {
1114 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(headerBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1115 return 0; //everytime a header changes return & check next time
1116 }
1117 }
1118 else
1119 {
1120 lastAdr = buffCmd[curChan][WRAPDEC(interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE)][1];
1121 headAdr = buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1];
1122 }
1123 while (TRUE == search4Cmd)
1124 {
1125 if (interpretBuffCmd[curChan] == writeBuffCmd[curChan])
1126 {
1127 i++;
1128 if(i < COMMAND_SOURCES)
1129 {
1130 curChan = orderBuffCmd[i];
1131 }
1132 else
1133 {
1134 return 0; //nothing to interpret
1135 }
1136 break; //check next availiable channel in outer while loop
1137 }
1138 uint8 curAdr = buffCmd[curChan][interpretBuffCmd[curChan]][1];
1139 if(curAdr == headAdr) //end of multibyte command
1140 {
1141 uint8 numDataBytes = ACTIVELEN(headerBuffCmd[curChan], interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1142 numDataBytes = ((numDataBytes & 0xC) << 4) | (numDataBytes & 3); //shifted to outer nibble
1143 if ( numDataBytes == ( CMD_NUM_BYTE_MASK & headAdr ))
1144 {
1145 search4Cmd = FALSE;
1146 }
1147 else
1148 {
1149 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1150 cntCmdError++;
1151 return -EILSEQ;
1152 }
1153 }
1154 else if (lastAdr == headAdr)
1155 {
1156 if (CMD_MAIN_FIRST_BYTE == curAdr)
1157 {
1158 lastAdr = curAdr; //byte inc correctly
1159 interpretBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1160 }
1161 else
1162 {
1163 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1164 cntCmdError++;
1165 return -EILSEQ;
1166 }
1167 }
1168 else
1169 {
1170 if (curAdr < lastAdr)
1171 {
1172 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1173 cntCmdError++;
1174 return -EILSEQ;
1175 }
1176 uint8 curAdrDiff = curAdr - lastAdr;
1177 switch (curAdrDiff)
1178 {
1179 case 1:
1180 break;
1181 case 61:
1182 if(3 == (lastAdr & 3))
1183 {
1184 break;//byte increment skipping middle address nibble
1185 }
1186 default:
1187 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1188 cntCmdError++;
1189 return -EILSEQ;
1190 }
1191 lastAdr = curAdr; //byte inc correctly
1192 interpretBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1193 }
1194 }
1195 }
1196
1197 }while(TRUE == search4Cmd);
1198
1199 uint8 cmdID = buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][0];
1200 uint8 curBuffCmd;
1201 switch(cmdID)
1202 {
1203 case 0x01 ... 0xF:
1204 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1205 {
1206 cntCmdError++;
1207 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1208 return -ENOEXEC;
1209 }
1210 hkSecs = cmdID & 0x0F;
1211 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1212 return 1;
1213 case 0x31 ... 0x3F:
1214 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1215 {
1216 cntCmdError++;
1217 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1218 return -ENOEXEC;
1219 }
1220 rtcStatus |= cmdID & 0x0F;
1221 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1222 return 1;
1223 case 0x40:
1224 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1225 {
1226 cntCmdError++;
1227 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1228 return -ENOEXEC;
1229 }
1230 cntError = 0;
1231 cntCmdError = 0;
1232 cntFramesDropped = 0;
1233 cntFramesDroppedUSB = 0;
1234 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1235 return 1;
1236 case 0x41:
1237 if (2 != ACTIVELEN(headerBuffCmd[curChan], interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE))
1238 {
1239 cntCmdError++;
1240 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1241 return -ENOEXEC;
1242 }
1243 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(headerBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1244 outputBusyLowThres = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 99;
1245 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1246 outputBusyHighThres = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 99;
1247 if (0 == outputBusyHighThres)
1248 {
1249 outputBusyHighThres = 1;
1250 }
1251 if (outputBusyLowThres > outputBusyHighThres)
1252 {
1253 outputBusyHighThres = outputBusyLowThres;
1254 }
1255 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1256 interpretBuffCmd[curChan] = headerBuffCmd[curChan];
1257 return 1;
1258 case 0x45:
1259 if (7 != ACTIVELEN(headerBuffCmd[curChan], interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE))
1260 {
1261 cntCmdError++;
1262 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1263 return -ENOEXEC;
1264 }
1265 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(headerBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1266 mainTimeDate.Sec = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 60;
1267 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1268 mainTimeDate.Min = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 60;
1269 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1270 mainTimeDate.Hour = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 24;
1271 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1272 mainTimeDate.DayOfMonth = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 31;
1273 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1274 mainTimeDate.Month = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0] % 12;
1275 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1276 mainTimeDate.Year = buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0];
1277 curBuffCmd = WRAPINC(curBuffCmd, CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1278 mainTimeDate.Year <<= 8;
1279 mainTimeDate.Year |= buffCmd[curChan][curBuffCmd][0];
1280 RTC_Main_WriteTime(&mainTimeDate);
1281// RTC_Main_Init();//Sets RTC variables DEBUG
1282 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = WRAPINC(interpretBuffCmd[curChan], CMD_BUFFER_SIZE);
1283 interpretBuffCmd[curChan] = headerBuffCmd[curChan];
1284 return 1;
1285 case 0x46:
1286 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1287 {
1288 cntCmdError++;
1289 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1290 return -ENOEXEC;
1291 }
1292 RTC_Main_Init();
1293 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1294 return 1;
1295 //47 is software reset main which completes in ISR
1296 case 0x48:
1297 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1298 {
1299 cntCmdError++;
1300 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1301 return -ENOEXEC;
1302 }
1303 Pin_Reset_Ev_HW_Write(0);
1304 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1305 return 1;
1306 case 0x49:
1307 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1308 {
1309 cntCmdError++;
1310 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1311 return -ENOEXEC;
1312 }
1313 Pin_Reset_Ev_SW_Write(1);
1314 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1315 return 1;
1316 case 0x4A:
1317 if (CMD_MAIN_PSOC_ADDRESS != buffCmd[curChan][headerBuffCmd[curChan]][1])
1318 {
1319 cntCmdError++;
1320 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1321 return -ENOEXEC;
1322 }
1323 SendInitCmds();
1324 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1325 return 1;
1326 default:
1327 break;
1328 }
1329 cntCmdError++;
1330 headerBuffCmd[curChan] = interpretBuffCmd[curChan];
1331 return -ENXIO;
1332}

1334uint8 CheckI2C()
1335{
1336 if( buffI2CRead != buffI2CWrite) //Check if any transactions
1337 {
1338 uint8 status;
1339
1340 status = I2C_RTC_MasterStatus();
1341 if( 0 == (status & I2C_RTC_MSTAT_XFER_INP )) //Check if busy
1342 {
1343
1344 uint8 errors;
1345 errors = (status & I2C_RTC_MSTAT_ERR_MASK);
1346
1347 //TODO handle completion and errors
1348 if( errors != 0)
1349 {
1350 buffI2C[buffI2CRead].error = errors;
1351 buffI2CRead = WRAPINC(buffI2CRead, I2C_BUFFER_SIZE);
1352 numI2CRetry = 0;
1353 cntError++;
1354 }
1355 else if ( 0 != (status & I2C_RTC_MSTAT_RD_CMPLT ))
1356 {
1357 if(I2C_READ == buffI2C[buffI2CRead].type)
1358 {
1359 buffI2C[buffI2CRead].error = 0;
1360 }
1361 else
1362 {
1363 buffI2C[buffI2CRead].error = I2C_RTC_MSTAT_ERR_MASK; //TODO new Error for thei mismatch
1364 cntError++;
1365 }
1366 buffI2CRead = WRAPINC(buffI2CRead, I2C_BUFFER_SIZE);
1367 numI2CRetry = 0;
1368 }
1369 else if ( 0 != (status & I2C_RTC_MSTAT_WR_CMPLT ))
1370 {
1371 if(I2C_WRITE == buffI2C[buffI2CRead].type)
1372 {
1373 buffI2C[buffI2CRead].error = 0;
1374 }
1375 else
1376 {
1377 buffI2C[buffI2CRead].error = I2C_RTC_MSTAT_ERR_MASK; //TODO new Error for thei mismatch
1378 cntError++;
1379 }
1380 buffI2CRead = WRAPINC(buffI2CRead, I2C_BUFFER_SIZE);
1381 numI2CRetry = 0;
1382 }
1383 else //execute new transacttion
1384 {
1385 if(I2C_WRITE == buffI2C[buffI2CRead].type)
1386 {
1387 errors = I2C_RTC_MasterWriteBuf(buffI2C[buffI2CRead].slaveAddress, buffI2C[buffI2CRead].data, buffI2C[buffI2CRead].cnt, buffI2C[buffI2CRead].mode);
1388 if (0 != errors)
1389 {
1390 cntError++;
1391 //TODO handle individual errors
1392 numI2CRetry++;
1393 }
1394 }
1395 else if(I2C_READ == buffI2C[buffI2CRead].type)
1396 {
1397 errors = I2C_RTC_MasterReadBuf(buffI2C[buffI2CRead].slaveAddress, buffI2C[buffI2CRead].data, buffI2C[buffI2CRead].cnt, buffI2C[buffI2CRead].mode);
1398 if (0 != errors)
1399 {
1400 cntError++;
1401 //TODO handle individual errors
1402 numI2CRetry++;
1403 }
1404 }
1405 if (I2C_MAX_RETRIES <= numI2CRetry)
1406 {
1407 buffI2C[buffI2CRead].error = errors;
1408 buffI2CRead = WRAPINC(buffI2CRead, I2C_BUFFER_SIZE);
1409 numI2CRetry = 0;
1410 }
1411 }
1412 }
1413 I2C_RTC_MasterClearStatus();
1414 }
1415
1416 return 0;
1417}

1566
1567 }
1568 else
1569 {

1572 if (MAIN_HK_I2C_BUFFER_SIZE <= mainHKI2CRead)

1575 uint32 temp32 = cntCmd;

1577 temp32 >>= 8;

1594 Pin_LED2_Write(outputBusy);
1595 }

1597 buffHK[buffHKWrite].framesDroppedRS232[1] = temp32 & 0xFF; //LSB of Dropped RS232 packets
1598 temp32 >>= 8;
1599 buffHK[buffHKWrite].framesDroppedRS232[0] = temp32 & 0xFF; //MSB of Dropped RS232 packets
1600 temp32 = cntFramesDroppedUSB;
1601 buffHK[buffHKWrite].framesDroppedUSB[1] = temp32 & 0xFF; //LSB of Dropped USB packets

1607 buffHK[buffHKWrite].coreDieTemp[1] = temp16 & 0xFF; //LSB of core temp
1608 temp16 >>= 8;
1609 buffHK[buffHKWrite].coreDieTemp[0] = temp16 & 0xFF; //MSB of core temp
1610 }
1611 else
1612 {
1613 buffHK[buffHKWrite].missingValuesThisPacket++;
1614 buffHK[buffHKWrite].coreDieTemp[0] = 0x80; //MSB of core temp, Max negative number is out-of-range error indicator
1615 buffHK[buffHKWrite].coreDieTemp[1] = 0x00; //LSB of core temp
1616 cntError++;// TODO could check specific error
1617 }
1618 buffHK[buffHKWrite].generalErrors = cntError;
1619 buffHKWrite = WRAPINC( buffHKWrite , HK_BUFFER_PACKETS );
1620 hkCollecting = FALSE;
1621 ForcedSampleBaroI2C(); //Force sample next Baro
1622 Pin_LED1_Write(0);
1623 return 1;
1624 }
1625 }while(continueCheck);
1626
1627 }
1628 else if ((TRUE == hkReq)) //see if req is made by ISRCheckBaro
1629 {
1630 Pin_LED1_Write(1);
1631 hkCollecting = TRUE;
1632 uint8 intState = CyEnterCriticalSection();
1633 hkReq = FALSE;
1634 CyExitCriticalSection(intState);
1635 //start specific data collection
1636// uint32 temp32 = curBaroTempCnt[0];
1638// int8 i=3; //32bit
1639// buffHK[buffHKWrite].baroTemp1[i] = temp32 & 0xFF; // to make this endian independent and output as big endian, fill the LSB first
1640// while (0 <= --i) //Fill the Higher order bytes

1642// temp32 >>= 8;
1643// buffHK[buffHKWrite].baroTemp1[i] = temp32 & 0xFF;

1793#define EV_DUMP_SIZE (EV_BUFFER_SIZE - WRAP(EV_BUFFER_SIZE, FRAME_DATA_BYTES))
1794#define EV_MIN_SIZE (9u)
1795#define EV_MAX_SIZE (255u + 9u) //max 1 byte len + addtional bytes
1796int8 CheckEventPackets()
1797{
1798 if ((buffEvWriteLast != buffEvWrite) && (buffEvRead != buffEvWrite) && ((WRAPINC(packetEvTail, PACKET_EVENT_SIZE) != packetEvHead))) //check for new active data in event buffer, and no overflow
1799 {
1800 EvBufferIndex curRead = buffEvRead;
1801 buffEvWriteLast = buffEvWrite;
1802 if (packetEvHead != packetEvTail) //check for queued packets to decide where to start
1803 {
1804 curRead = WRAPINC( packetEv[ WRAPDEC(packetEvTail, PACKET_EVENT_SIZE) ].EOR , EV_BUFFER_SIZE); //move active past last packet found
1805 }
1806 EvBufferIndex startRead = curRead; //store the largest search bound for comparison later
1807// EvBufferIndex curEOR = WRAPDEC(buffEvWrite, EV_BUFFER_SIZE);
1808 EvBufferIndex nBytes = ACTIVELEN(curRead, buffEvWrite, EV_BUFFER_SIZE);
1809 if (EV_DUMP_SIZE <= nBytes)
1810 {
1811 uint8 tmpPacketEvTail = packetEvTail;
1812 packetEvTail = WRAPINC(packetEvTail, PACKET_EVENT_SIZE);
1813 packetEv[tmpPacketEvTail].header = curRead;
1814 packetEv[tmpPacketEvTail].EOR = WRAP( curRead + (EV_DUMP_SIZE - 1), EV_BUFFER_SIZE); // inclusive so -1 to the dump size
1815
1816 return 1;
1817 }
1818 EvBufferIndex curEOR = WRAPDEC(buffEvWrite, EV_BUFFER_SIZE);// make inclusive
1819 while (EV_MIN_SIZE <= nBytes) //min packet size is smallest search space
1820 {
1821 if(frame00FF[1] == buffEv[curEOR])
1822 {
1823 EvBufferIndex iterRev = WRAPDEC(curEOR, EV_BUFFER_SIZE); //iterator to check prev bytes
1824 if(frame00FF[0] == buffEv[iterRev])
1825 {
1826
1827 if(EOR_HEAD == buffEv[ WRAPDEC(iterRev, EV_BUFFER_SIZE)]) //last 3 bytes should be EOR 0xFF00FF
1828 {
1829
1830 EvBufferIndex expBytes = ACTIVELEN(curRead, curEOR, EV_BUFFER_SIZE) + 1; //expected bytes to check packet structure, +1 inclusive
1831 iterRev = WRAP(expBytes, 3); //calc number of bytes off 3 byte alignment and temp store in iterRev (done with EOR checks)
1832 if (0 != iterRev) //check if misaligned search space
1833 {
1834// iterRev = (3 - iterRev); //calc number of bytes needed to get on 3 byte alignment
1835 if (iterRev < expBytes)//prevent underflow
1836 {
1837 expBytes -= iterRev; //reduce byte expectation to 3 byte alignment
1838// nBytes -= iterRev; //reduce num byte to 3 byte alignment
1839 curRead = WRAP( curRead + iterRev, EV_BUFFER_SIZE); //move read into 3 byte alignment
1840 }
1841 }
1842 if (EV_MAX_SIZE < expBytes)
1843 {
1844 curRead = WRAP( (EV_BUFFER_SIZE - EV_MAX_SIZE) + 1 + curEOR, EV_BUFFER_SIZE);//max search space for header, + 1 inclusive
1845 expBytes = EV_MAX_SIZE; // now expecting the max size packet, will keep reducing by 3
1846// nBytes = EV_MAX_SIZE; // now expecting the max size packet, will keep reducing by 3
1847 }
1848 while (EV_MIN_SIZE <= expBytes) //min packet size is smallest search space
1849 {
1850 EvBufferIndex calcBytes = EV_MIN_SIZE; //data bytes in fixed packet, excludes header & EOR
1851 switch (buffEv[curRead])
1852 {
1853 case EVVAR_HEAD:
1854 calcBytes = buffEv[ WRAP3INC(curRead, EV_BUFFER_SIZE)] + 9u;// valid data bytes in packet, might not be multiple of 3. Add for header, EOR, & len
1855 case EVFIX_HEAD: //EVVAR_HEAD continues here
1856 if (((expBytes - 2u) <= calcBytes) && ((expBytes) >= calcBytes)) //3 byte range for the listed len compared to actual
1857 {
1858 EvBufferIndex iterFwd = WRAPINC( curRead, EV_BUFFER_SIZE); //iterator to check next bytes
1859 if(frame00FF[0] == buffEv[iterFwd])
1860 {
1861 if(frame00FF[1] == buffEv[WRAPINC( iterFwd, EV_BUFFER_SIZE)]) //header is in curRead position, packet location and bookend checked
1862 {
1863 uint8 numPkts = 0;
1864// uint8 intState = CyEnterCriticalSection(); //TODO consider the mutex
1865 if (curRead != startRead)// check if data that failed checks precededs the header
1866 {
1867 uint8 tmpPacketEvTail = packetEvTail;
1868 packetEvTail = WRAPINC(packetEvTail, PACKET_EVENT_SIZE); //dumping the unchecked data
1869 packetEv[tmpPacketEvTail].header = startRead; //start with beginning of active bytes
1870 packetEv[tmpPacketEvTail].EOR = WRAPDEC( curRead , EV_BUFFER_SIZE); // 1 byte before Read ends dump
1871 numPkts++;
1872 }
1873// CyExitCriticalSection(intState); //TODO consider the mutex
1874 if ((WRAPINC(packetEvTail, PACKET_EVENT_SIZE) != packetEvHead)) //check if space for another packet
1875 {
1876 uint8 tmpPacketEvTail = packetEvTail;
1877 packetEvTail = WRAPINC(packetEvTail, PACKET_EVENT_SIZE); //dumping the unchecked data
1878 packetEv[tmpPacketEvTail].header = curRead; //start with found header
1879 packetEv[tmpPacketEvTail].EOR = curEOR; // found EOR
1880 numPkts++;
1881 }
1882 return numPkts;
1883 }
1884 }
1885 }
1886 break;
1887 }
1888 expBytes -= 3; //shrink search space by 3
1889 curRead = WRAP3INC(curRead, EV_BUFFER_SIZE); //move forward along 3 byte alignment
1890 }
1891 return 0; // give up after first potential EOR found to limit loop time (stay order n). will dump this out eventually & will processed by a PC (more CPU & time)
1892 }
1893 }
1894 }
1895
1896 nBytes--; //shrink search space
1897 curEOR = WRAPDEC(curEOR, EV_BUFFER_SIZE); //Move back to check next byte
1898// nBytes = ACTIVELEN(curRead, curEOR, EV_BUFFER_SIZE) + 1; //shrink search space to new endpoints, +1 inclusive
1899
1900 }
1901
1902
1903 }
1904 return 0;
